STATE of North Carolina
v.
Lionel Lamont COX. No. 200P98-2. Supreme Court of North Carolina. August 17, 2006. Lionel Lamont Cox, Pro Se. John G. Barnwell, Assistant Attorney General, C. Branson Vickory, III, District Attorney, for State of NC.

ORDER

Upon consideration of the petition filed by Defendant on the 31st day of May 2006 in this matter for a writ of certiorari to review the order of the Superior Court, Wayne County, the following order was entered and is hereby certified to the Superior Court of that County:

"Dismissed by order of the Court in conference, this the 17th day of August 2006."
